# @FORMAT NAME|KIND|VISIBILITY|RETURN|PARAMS|DESCRIPTION
# Sample GDLC fixture — code structure for a parser module

@D src/lib/parsers|Parser modules for GDL format family

@T GdlsParser|Parses GDLS schema files into structured types
parseGdlsFile|function|public|GdlsFile|content: string|Main entry point for GDLS parsing
parseDomain|function|private|GdlsDomain|line: string|Extracts @D domain header
parseColumn|function|private|GdlsColumn|line: string|Parses positional column fields
normalizeType|function|private|string|raw: string|Normalizes SQL type names
TABLE_PATTERN|const|private|RegExp||Regex matching @T lines
GdlsFile|interface|public|||Parsed schema result type
@E GdlsColumn.nullable|Y,N|Whether column allows nulls
@R GdlsParser -> GdlsFile|returns
@R GdlsParser -> fs|depends|Reads .gdls files from filesystem
@R GdlsParser.parseColumn -> GdlsParser.normalizeType|calls

@T GdlParser|Parses GDL data record files
parseGdl|function|public|GdlRecord[]|content: string|Parses pipe-delimited data records
getField|function|public|string \| null|record: string, key: string|Extracts key:value field from record
splitFields|function|public|string[]|record: string|Splits record respecting escape sequences
@R GdlParser -> GdlsParser|imports|Reuses shared type definitions
@R GdlParser.getField -> GdlParser.splitFields|calls

@D src/components|UI components for GDL Explorer

@T GdlsViewer|Main GDLS schema viewer component
GdlsViewerProps|interface|public|||Component props type
selectedTable|property|private|string \| null||Currently selected table name
viewMode|property|private|string||Tree or ER diagram mode
@E GdlsViewer.viewMode|tree,er|Display mode toggle
@R GdlsViewer -> GdlsParser|imports|Consumes parsed schema data
@R GdlsViewer -> SchemaTree|calls|Renders tree navigation
@R GdlsViewer -> TableDetail|calls|Renders table detail panel

@T TableDetail|Shows columns, FKs, and enum values for a table
TableDetailProps|interface|public|||Component props type
onTableNavigate|method|public|void|tableName: string|Navigates to another table
@R TableDetail -> GdlsViewer|imports

@PATH Request -> ApiRoute -> GdlsParser -> FileSystem|callchain|Schema load flow
@PATH UserClick -> GdlsViewer -> SchemaTree -> TableDetail|dataflow|Table navigation
